  "text": "Firefox crashes when processing CSS calc() expressions with extreme numeric values due to unprotected floating-point arithmetic that overflows to infinity or NaN. The vulnerability spans CSS calc() parsing through computed value resolution.\n\n## Parsing Layer\nCSS calc() expressions are parsed in `servo/components/style/values/specified/calc.rs`, which contains the `CalcNode` enum and parsing logic for mathematical functions including calc(), min(), max(), clamp(), and other CSS math functions. This file handles the initial syntactic parsing of calc() strings.\n\n## Calc Expression Structure\nThe `GenericCalcNode` in `servo/components/style/values/generics/calc.rs` defines the abstract syntax tree for calc expressions. It supports various operations: Sum, Product, MinMax, Clamp, Round, ModRem, and trigonometric functions. This generic structure is used for both specified and computed values.\n\n## Numeric Overflow Issues\n\n### Root Cause: Unprotected Arithmetic in Computed Values\nThe critical overflow vulnerability occurs in `servo/components/style/values/computed/length_percentage.rs` in the `CalcLengthPercentageLeaf` trait implementation:\n\n1. **try_sum_in_place()** (line 796-832): Performs addition with plain `+=` operator (line 815) without overflow checking. For example:\n   ```rust\n   *one += *other;  // Plain float addition, can overflow to infinity\n   ```\n\n2. **try_product_in_place()** (line 834-858): Performs multiplication with plain `*=` operator (line 838) without bounds checking:\n   ```rust\n   *left *= *right;  // Plain float multiplication, can overflow\n   ```\n\n3. **try_op()** (line 860-883): Applies arbitrary operations to leaf values, including the result at line 870:\n   ```rust\n   Length(super::Length::new(op(one.px(), other.px())))  // op can produce infinity/NaN\n   ```\n\n4. **map()** (line 885-897): Applies a function to leaf values without validation of the result.\n\n### Resolution Chain\nThe resolution process in `GenericCalcNode::resolve_internal()` (`servo/components/style/values/generics/calc.rs`, line 928) performs arithmetic operations without overflow protection:\n\n- Line 950: `result = result.try_op(&right, |left, right| left + right)?;` for Sum nodes\n- Line 965/971: `result.map(|v| v * left)?;` for Product nodes\n\nThese operations chain together, and when extreme values are provided in calc() expressions (e.g., `calc(10e308 * 10e308)`), they produce infinity or NaN values.\n\n### Clamping Limitations\nWhile `AllowedNumericType::clamp()` in `servo/components/style_traits/values.rs` (lines 593-599) provides post-computation clamping, it only clamps based on the allowed numeric type (All, NonNegative, AtLeastOne, ZeroToOne). This clamping happens AFTER overflow has already occurred:\n\n```rust\nLength::new(self.clamping_mode.clamp(px.px())).normalized()  // Line 1004 in length_percentage.rs\n```\n\nOnce a value has overflowed to infinity, `clamp()` cannot recover the original intent.\n\n## C++ Integration Points\n\nThe Servo Rust code integrates with C++ Firefox through:\n\n1. **FFI Gateway** (`servo/ports/geckolib/glue.rs`, line 9208):\n   ```rust\n   pub extern \"C\" fn Servo_ResolveCalcLengthPercentage(\n       calc: &computed::length_percentage::CalcLengthPercentage,\n       basis: f32,\n   ) -> f32 {\n       calc.resolve(computed::Length::new(basis)).px()  // Calls resolve() which can overflow\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **C++ Resolution** (`layout/style/ServoStyleConstsInlines.h`, lines 726-735):\n   ```cpp\n   CSSCoord StyleCalcLengthPercentage::ResolveToCSSPixels(CSSCoord aBasis) const {\n       return Servo_ResolveCalcLengthPercentage(this, aBasis);  // Calls unprotected Rust resolution\n   }\n   ```\n\n## Summary of Vulnerable Files\n\n**Parsing**: `servo/components/style/values/specified/calc.rs` - parses CSS calc() syntax\n\n**Calc Tree Structure**: `servo/components/style/values/generics/calc.rs` - defines expression AST and resolution logic\n\n**Numeric Computation & Overflow**: `servo/components/style/values/computed/length_percentage.rs` - contains unprotected arithmetic operations (try_sum_in_place, try_product_in_place, try_op, map)\n\n**Clamping**: `servo/components/style_traits/values.rs` - provides post-computation clamping that cannot fix pre-existing overflow\n\n**FFI Bridge**: `servo/ports/geckolib/glue.rs` - Servo_ResolveCalcLengthPercentage function that calls vulnerable Rust code\n\n**C++ Integration**: `layout/style/ServoStyleConstsInlines.h` - StyleCalcLengthPercentage::Resolve methods that invoke the FFI\n\nThe crash occurs because extreme calc() values overflow during intermediate arithmetic operations, producing infinity or NaN, which then cause issues downstream in Firefox's layout or rendering pipeline."
}

